# Momora AI Pipelines

Functions (names are fixed — extend, don't rename):

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `generate-portrait-illustration` | Character portrait on profile save |
| `analyze-emotion` | Emotion + palette from memory text |
| `generate-illustration` | Memory illustration with portrait refs |
| `process-voice-memory` | Transcribe + tag + cleanup |

## Flow rules

1. **Portraits** at profile save; **illustrations** after memory save.
2. Safety pre-check memory text before image generation; retry once on moderation block.
3. Resolve `illustration_style` token → style reference URL from `public-assets`.
4. Use `gpt-image-2`, fallback `gpt-image-1`.
5. Update status columns before/after async work (`generating` → `ready`|`failed`).
6. Delete superseded illustration/portrait objects on regeneration.

## Voice pipeline

1. Transcribe with family name/nickname prompt context.
2. Parse names → `mentionedMemberIds`.
3. LLM cleanup + self-reference → add user profile id if needed.
4. Return `{ cleanedText, mentionedMemberIds }` — never store audio.

## Shared code

Put prompts and style maps in `_shared/prompts.ts`, `_shared/styles.ts` — avoid duplicating strings across functions.
